nA reorganization of the Bonn cabinet will soon be announced.\n\nIn the main shifts, Vice Chancellor Bluecher would be replaced by Karl Arnold, former minister president of the important industrial state of North Rhine Westphalia. This shift would conciliate the left-wing element of the Christian Democratic Party and offset the demotion of unpopular Defense Minister Blank, a trade union man, to the Labor Ministry post. Blank is to be replaced by Minister of Atomic Affairs Strauss, a move possibly foreshadowing greater emphasis on atomic rather than conventional weapons for the West German army.\n\nMeanwhile, Minister Blank is disturbed and believes Adenauer may give in to increasing pressure to replace him. Blank made no mention of any decision having been reached at the recent cabinet meeting, and states that the whole matter of a cabinet reshuffle will be discussed by Adenauer and coalition leaders on 11 October in Berlin", "token_count": 156, "token_end_0based": 155, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "1 west german cabinet shake-up may be imminent a reorganization of the bonn cabinet will soon be announced in the main shifts vice chancellor bluecher would be replaced by karl arnold former minister president of the important industrial state of north rhine westphalia this shift would conciliate the left-wing element of the christian democratic party and offset the demotion of unpopular defense minister blank a trade union man to the labor ministry post blank is to be replaced by minister of atomic affairs strauss a move possibly foreshadowing greater emphasis on atomic rather than conventional weapons for the west german army meanwhile minister blank is disturbed and believes adenauer may give in to increasing pressure to replace him blank made no mention of any decision having been reached at the recent cabinet meeting and states that the whole matter of a cabinet reshuffle will be discussed by adenauer and coalition leaders on 11 october in berlin", "unred_source_page": 3}
